main event: An unidentified flying object was observed over Wichita Falls, Texas on 11 May 1961.
interesting points: Several persons reported seeing a bright light in the sky at about 2100 hours, The light was observed for about 30 minutes and described as much larger than a star, changing colors and moving erratically, The object's shape was described as round and white, resembling a star, The object was estimated to be at least 50,000 feet and moving at a high speed, There were no aircraft in the area that could have been mistaken for the object.
sighted object: a bright light in the sky
witness description: Delshad or Dilshal, Airman 5 in the 8th Weather Group
